The Canadian Parliament nevertheless approved a resolution on the Palestinian issue.
The House of Representatives calls on the government to:

(a) demand an immediate ceasefire, the release of all hostages, and Hamas must lay down its arms;

(b) stop further authorizations and transfers of arms exports to Israel to ensure compliance with Canada's arms export regime and increase efforts to stop the illicit arms trade, including with Hamas;

(c) ensure continued funding for the United Nations Relief and Work Agency to meet urgent humanitarian needs, participate in the UN's internal investigation and independent review, and ensure that necessary long-term management reforms and accountability measures are implemented;

(d) support the prosecution of all crimes and violations of international law committed in the region;

(e) support the work of the International Court of Justice and the International Criminal Court;

(f) demand unhindered humanitarian access to Gaza;

(g) ensure that Canadians stranded in Gaza can achieve safety in Canada and expand access to the temporary resident visa program;

(h) apply sanctions against extremist settlers and maintain sanctions against Hamas leaders;

(i) reaffirm that settlements are illegal under international law and that settlements and settler violence are serious obstacles to a negotiated two-state solution, and advocate for an end to the decades-long occupation of Palestinian territories; And

(j) work with international partners to actively pursue the goal of a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the Middle East, including towards the establishment of a State of Palestine as part of a negotiated two-state solution, and support Canada's position that Israel has a right to exist in peace and security with its neighbors.
